  "jobTitle": "Independent Researcher",
  "description": "Andreas Ehstand is an independent researcher and the originator and sole author of the AUGMANITAI corpus, the first systematic descriptive-terminology framework for human-AI interaction phenomena: 204 operationally-defined terms written in an ISO 704 / ISO 1087 descriptive-terminology style and organized as a periodic-table-style taxonomy across roughly ten domains, openly published under CC BY 4.0 and archived on Zenodo. The corpus is a reference vocabulary that names and operationally defines interaction phenomena, and it cross-walks to established constructs it relates to, including flow (Csikszentmihalyi), tacit knowledge (Polanyi), technology acceptance (UTAUT / Davis), cognitive load (NASA-TLX, Sweller), and experience sampling. Background: over a decade of high-performance sport coaching in tennis and padel; alumnus of the University of Bayreuth and TU Dortmund; holder of a Bavarian university-teaching certificate (FBZHL) and of the EU trademark License of Clarity (EUIPO 019206780). ORCID 0009-0006-3773-7796; Wikidata Q138634675.",
  "knowsAbout": [
    "AUGMANITAI corpus (originator and sole author)",
    "Descriptive terminology for human-AI interaction phenomena",
    "ISO 704 terminology work",
    "ISO 1087 vocabulary",
    "ISO 30042 TermBase eXchange",
    "Operationally-defined terminology",
    "Periodic-table-style terminology taxonomy",
